abstract: THE screenplay for "Honeysuckle Rose" is credited to three writers, and what they  have created is dialogue, not conversation. The film's four editors have put together sequences, not scenes.

abstract: A walk through New York City streets felt like a stroll through a steambath yesterday as residents sweated through 99degree heat, the hottest July 16 on record. An unrelenting sun, high humidity and a hazy cloud cover added to the discomfort, unrelieved even by occasional 10 mile-anhour breezes.
headline_main: New Yorkers Swelter as 99 Temperature Breaks 101-Year-Old Record
